        "timestamp": "2019-12-19 20:15:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nThey look cleaner junit tests with nice @Before, @BeforeClass and @AfterClass use. Thanks, Liam! \n\nOne concern I have is, I am pretty sure that the coverage will drop as we test all the 200 cases, but not 404, 400 and 419 cases, particularly for ApiRestController I mean. Half of the code in ApiRestController is for non-200 cases (caught exception). Like you said, we can design new test cases to cover them. Should be easier to do with cleaner test structure now.",
